     This method should be invoked on the parent object to abandon its relationship with one or more
children.
<p/>
Ths method removes all Relation objects where the parent is this object and the child_id, child_label
and relation_name have the values passed in as parameters. You can make the query more generic by
passing <CODE>null</CODE> as the value for either <CODE>childId</CODE>, or <CODE>childLabel</CODE>, or
both. For example, if both <CODE>childId</CODE> and <CODE>childLabel</CODE> are <CODE>null</CODE>, all
relation objects where the relation type is <CODE>relationTypeName</CODE> and the parent is this object
will be removed.

@param relationTypeName - name of the relation.
@param childId          - child of this object.
@param childLabel       - version string of the child.

