@throws DfException

      Executes a DQL query. <P>
 Before  calling this method, assign a DQL statement to the query with
 the <CODE>setDQL</CODE> method. Refer to the <EM>Server DQL Reference Manual</EM>
 for more information about DQL statements. <P>
 <P>
 The following code example demonstrates how to obtain an IDfQuery interface, set a DQL
 query to the object, execute the query, then spin through the result set:
 <P><HR><BLOCKQUOTE><PRE>
 IDfQuery q = new DfQuery();
 q.setDQL("select * from dm_cabinet");
 IDfCollection col = q.execute(sess, DfQuery.DF_READ_QUERY);
 while (col.next())
 {
      // Spin through the attributes...
      for (int i = 0; i < col.getAttrCount(); i++)
      {
          IDfAttr attr = col.getAttr(i);
          System.out.print("Attribute Name: " + attr.getName());
      }
 }
 col.close();
 </PRE></BLOCKQUOTE><HR>

 @param	session the current session
 @param	queryType  the type of query that you want to execute;
 The following list specifies the integer corresponding to all query types:
 <PRE>
 <B>Integer</B>	   <B>Query Type</B>
 0		   READ QUERY
 1		   QUERY
 2		   CACHE QUERY
 3		   EXECUTE QUERY
 4		   EXECUTE READ QUERY
 5		   APPLY
 </PRE><P>
 @return an IDfCollection interface to the query results.
 @exception  DfException	if the query fails to execute or if the specified
			   session has timed out and cannot be re-established.
 @see #setDQL

