@throws DfException if the query failed

     Retrieves the work items assigned to the specified user. This method is available to Documentum server version
5.0 or above.

@param userName      the user whose tasks you want to retrieve.
@param filter        any combination of: {@link #DF_NOTIFICATIONS}, {@link #DF_WORKFLOW_TASKS}, {@link
                     #DF_ROUTER_TASKS}, or {@link #DF_COMPLETED_ROUTER_TASKS}. These categories should be bitwise
                     OR'ed together when you need to retrieve the tasks of multiple categories.<P> Other filters
                     used for getTasks {@link #DF_TASKS} and {@link #DF_TASKS_AND_NOTIFICATIONS} are also
                     supported in this function. If {@link #DF_TASKS} is used, it is treated as {@link
                     #DF_WORKFLOW_TASKS}|{@link #DF_ROUTER_TASKS}. If {@link #DF_TASKS_AND_NOTIFICATIONS} is
                     used, all kinds of items will be returned.
@param orderByList   an {@link IDfList} of the task attributes that are used to order the retrieved tasks.
@param ascendingList an {@link IDfList} of Boolean values to specify whether the corresponding order by attribute
                     should be sorted in ascending or descending order. Specify <CODE>true</CODE> for ascending
                     order; <CODE>false</CODE> for descending order.

@return an IDfCollection interface containing all attributes of the user's queue item and pkg_object_id,
        pkg_object_name, pkg_object_type, pkg_content_type, pkg_application_type, pkg_link_cnt, pkg_lock_owner,
        and pkg_is_virtual_doc queried from the corresponding attribute of the routing document.

@throws DfException if the query failed.
@since 5.1

     Creates and starts a custom workflow.
<p/>
Use this method when you want to create and start a workflow that is not based on a pre-defined workflow
template. Refer to the <EM>Server Fundamentals</EM> for more information about workflows.
<p/>
The following code example demonstrates how to route an object to a user and a group:
<P><HR><BLOCKQUOTE><PRE>
IDfList userList = new DfList();
IDfList groupList = new DfList();
IDfList objList = new DfList();
userList.appendString("joeuser");
groupList.appendString("EngineeringGroup");
objList.append(new DfId("0900d5bb8001f900"));
IDfId wfId = sess.sendToDistributionList(userList,groupList,"Please review",objList,5,false);
</PRE></BLOCKQUOTE><HR>

@param toUsers      an IDfList interface to the users that are assigned workflow tasks.
@param toGroups     an IDfList interface to the groups that are assigned workflow tasks.
@param instructions task instructions for the recipients of workflow tasks.
@param objectIDs    an IDfList interface to the documents you want to distribute. You may only distribute
                    persistent objects in a workflow.
@param priority     An integer value corresponding to the priority level. The following list explains the
                    priority level corresponding to all permissible values:<p/>
<PRE>
<B>Integer</B>    <B>Priority Level</B>
1          Low
5          Medium
10         High</PRE>

@param endNotification defines whether a notification is sent to the sender of the distribution list when all the
                       recipients have finished their assigned task.

@return an IDfId interface to the custom workflow.

@throws DfException if the server fails to create the custom workflow.
@deprecated As of DFC 5.2, replaced by {@link #sendToDistributionListEx(com.documentum.fc.common.IDfList,
            com.documentum.fc.common.IDfList, java.lang.String, com.documentum.fc.common.IDfList, int, int)}

     Creates and starts an ad-hoc workflow.
<p/>
Use this method when you want to create and start a workflow that is not based on a workflow template. Refer to
the <EM>Server Fundamentals</EM> for more information about workflows.
<p/>
The following code example demonstrates how to route an object to a user and a group:
<P><HR><BLOCKQUOTE><PRE>
IDfList userList = new DfList();
IDfList groupList = new DfList();
IDfList objList = new DfList();
userList.appendString("joeuser");
groupList.appendString("EngineeringGroup");
objList.append(new DfId("0900d5bb8001f900"));
int flags = DF_REQ_SIGN_OFF | DF_REQ_END_NOTIFICATION;
IDfId wfId = sess.sendToDistributionListEx(userList,groupList,"Please review",objList,5,flags);
</PRE></BLOCKQUOTE><HR>

@param toUsers      an IDfList interface to the users that are assigned workflow tasks.
@param toGroups     an IDfList interface to the groups that are assigned workflow tasks.
@param instructions task instructions for the recipients of workflow tasks.
@param objectIDs    an IDfList interface to the documents you want to the specified users and groups. You may
                    only distribute persistent objects in a workflow.
@param priority     An integer value corresponding to the priority level. The following list maps the valid
                    values to their corresponding priority levels:
<PRE>
<B>Integer</B>    <B>Priority Level</B>
1          Low
5          Medium
10         High</PRE>

@param flags Flags can be any combination of these options {@link IDfWorkflow#DF_REQ_END_NOTIFICATION}, {@link
             IDfWorkflow#DF_REQ_SIGN_OFF}, {@link IDfWorkflow#DF_SEQUENTIAL}, {@link
             IDfWorkflow#DF_ALLOW_REJECT_PREVIOUS}, and {@link IDfWorkflow#DF_ALLOW_REJECT_INITIATOR} bitwise
             OR'ed together.

@return an IDfId interface to the ad-hoc workflow.

@throws DfException if the server fails to create the ad-hoc workflow.
@see IDfWorkflow#DF_REQ_END_NOTIFICATION
@see IDfWorkflow#DF_REQ_SIGN_OFF
@see IDfWorkflow#DF_SEQUENTIAL
@see IDfWorkflow#DF_ALLOW_REJECT_PREVIOUS
@see IDfWorkflow#DF_ALLOW_REJECT_INITIATOR
@since 5.1

     Returns a collection that contains the object ID and attribute values of all installed dm_process objects in a
repository.
<p/>
Documentum uses dm_process objects to store workflow definitions in a repository. After a workflow is defined in a
process object, the object must be validated and installed before it is usable. Refer to <EM>Server
Fundamentals</EM> for more information about workflows.

@param additionalAttributes The additional attributes of the workflows that you want to retrieve.

@return An IDfCollection interface to the object name, object ID, and user-specified additional attributes of all
        installed workflow definitions in the repository

@throws DfException if the query failed

