     This methods indicates to the server to start gathering the metrics that have been passed in
to this method. The metrics should be in the format <code>componentIdentifer@metric</code> where
componentIdentifier is CS i.e. Content Server. If no componentIdentifier is specified it will still pick CS.
Please lookup the server administration manual for the names of metrics that can be gathered.

@param metricsToGather a list of metrics in the above mentioned format to start gathering
@return IDfCollection with attributes specifying whether the operation was successful or not and
        a repeating attribute specifying the list for which gathering has been started
@throws DfException if an error occurs while gathering metrics

     This methods indicates to the server to stop gathering the metrics that have been passed in
to this method. The metrics should be in the format <code>componentIdentifer@metric</code> where
componentIdentifier is CS i.e Content Server. If no componentIdentifier is specified it still defaults to CS.
Please lookup the server administration manual for the names of metrics that can be gathered.

@param metricsToStop a list of metrics in the above mentioned format to stop gathering
@return IDfCollection with attributes specifying whether the operation was successful or not and
        a repeating attribute specifying the list for which gathering has been stopped
@throws DfException if an error occurs while gathering metrics

     This methods indicates to the server to collect the metrics that have been passed in
to this method. The metrics should be in the format <code>componentIdentifer@metric</code> where
componentIdentifier is CS i.e. Content Server. If no componentIdentifier is specified it will still pick Content Server.
Please lookup the server administration manual for the names of metrics that can be gathered.

@param metricsToCollect a list of metrics in the above mentioned format to collect
@return IDfCollection with attributes specifying whether the operation was successful or not and
        a repeating attribute whose name is the name of the metric and whose value is the metric itself
@throws DfException if an error occurs while gathering metrics

     This is for resetting the metrics. This is for clearing the counters for restarting  metrics gathering. This is
also used to free up memory on the server associated with gathering metrics. So it is recommended that this
method be called once all the necessary metrics gathering has been completed.

@return a boolean which when TRUE indicates that the reset was successful and when FALSE it means reset failed
@throws DfException if an error occured while resetting metrics

     Sets the identity for &quot;manual&quot; user authentication. The identity must not already exist in the session
manager's idenity list, otherwise an exception is thrown. Use "clearIdentity" first if you want to overwrite in
any case.

@param docbase  repository name
@param identity IDfLoginInfo object set to the user credentials for that repository, like user name and password.

@throws DfServiceException Identity for this repository is already set.

     Takes the repository name as an argument and throws an exception on bad user credentials. No session handle is
returned. (The DFC session object is cached)

@param docbase repository name

@throws DfIdentityException       Identity not properly defined
@throws DfAuthenticationException Bad user credentials
@throws DfPrincipalException      Principal session problem
@throws DfServiceException        Cannot release session

     To get the session handle a service implementation should call the <CODE>getSession</CODE> method. The session
can be retrieved as many times as required. When the client is done the session must be released using the
<CODE>release</CODE> method.  If an <CODE>IDfSession</CODE> has not been established for the the specified
repository, a new session is automatically created.

@param docbase repository name

@throws DfIdentityException       Identity not properly defined (principal or identity for given repository).
                                  getMessage() returns repository name.
@throws DfAuthenticationException Bad user credentials
@throws DfPrincipalException      Principal session problem
@throws DfServiceException        Cannot release session

     To get a new instance of a DFC session, <CODE>newSession</CODE> retrieves a new session for the given repository.
Again, a client is responsible for releasing this session after its use.

@param docbase repository name

@throws DfIdentityException       Identity not properly defined (principal or identity for given repository).
                                  getMessage() returns repository name.
@throws DfAuthenticationException Bad user credentials
@throws DfPrincipalException      Principal session problem
@throws DfServiceException        Cannot release session

     Puts the DFC session object back into the session pool.  You should call this method as soon as you are finished
with objects in that session.

@param session DFC session object

     Commits all changes to the repositories currently accessed. <P> This commit is ignored (and changed to an
<CODE>abortTransaction</CODE>) if the <CODE>setTransactionRollbackOnly</CODE> method has been called.

@throws DfServiceException Internal problems

     Unlocks sessions currently locked (<CODE>beginClientControl</CODE>); must be called in order to allow the session
manager to be able to pool the sessions again.

