@exception DfException if a server error occurs.

     Assigns an ACL object to the object. <P>
An ACL is assigned to an object when it is created. The ACL
can remain with the object for the life of the object, or you
can replace the ACL with a call to <CODE>setACL</CODE>.
<P>
The following code example demonstrates how to assign a private ACL to
an object, then reset the object back to the original ACL settings:
<P><HR><BLOCKQUOTE><PRE>
IDfSysObject sysObj = (IDfSysObject)sess.getObject(new DfId("0900d5bb8001fd49"));
IDfACL oldACL = sysObj.getACL();
IDfACL newACL = sess.getACL(sess.getLoginUserName(), "MyPrivateACL");
sysObj.setACL(newACL);
sysObj.save();
sysObj.setACL(oldACL);
sysObj.save();
</PRE></BLOCKQUOTE><HR>

