     Rates a result. The result is rated according to its relevancy to the query 
definition associated with this IDfResultRater.

@param resultEntry The result to rate.
@return The result rate (a real number within the range 0 to 1).

     Gets the relative weight of an attribute when rating a result. The weight of an attribute is a positive number,
and is always relative to the other attributes weight. A weight of 0 negates the effect of the attribute. The
neutral weight is 1. For example, if 'object_name' is given a weight=2 and 'subject' is given a weight=1, then
'object_name' is twice as much important as 'subject', but 'object_name' alone is not given a bonus score.
<br>Note: use {@link #isAttributeValueRequired(String)} to check whether the attribute value(s) is required or if
a <code>null</code> value is sufficient.

@param attrName   The name of the attribute.
@param attrValues The values of the attribute (more than one value in the case of a repeated attribute). In many
                  cases the value is not required, see {@link #isAttributeValueRequired(String)}.
@return The attribute relative weight (a positive real number, the neutral weight is 1).

     Indicates whether the value(s) of attributes must be provided to the method {@link #getAttributeWeight}. If this
method returns <code>false</code> then a <code>null</code> value may be provided as parameter of {@link
#getAttributeWeight}.

@param attrName The name of the attribute.
@return <code>true</code>, if the attribute value(s) must be provided; <code>false</code> if a <code>null</code>
        value is sufficient.

     Indicates whether an attribute is part of the "full-text" definition. The "full-text" definition is the
association of a set of attributes to which the full-text constraints are matched. For example, if 'object_name'
and 'abstract' are full-text attributes, then a constraint on full-text will be analyzed in both 'object_name'
and 'abstract'.

@param attrName The name of the attribute.
@return <code>true</code>, if the attribute is a full-text one; <code>false</code>, otherwise.

     Indicates whether an attribute is primary. A primary attribute has a special meaning when computing results rate.
It is an important attribute of a result that contains the main characteristics of the result. Generally the
primary attribute is 'object_name'.

@param attrName The name of the attribute.
@return <code>true</code>, if the attribute is primary; <code>false</code>, otherwise.

     Gets the date attribute. This attribute contains the result creation date, it may be checked to analyze the
currency of the result. Generally the date attribute is 'r_modify_date'.

@return The date attribute name; or <code>null</code> if none.

     Indicates whether an attribute belongs to the result header. A header attribute is often consulted first to
determine roughly the content of the document. Generally header attributes are 'object_name', 'subject',
'summary', 'abstract', 'keywords'.

@param attrName The name of the attribute.
@return <code>true</code>, if the attribute belongs to the result header; <code>false</code>, otherwise.

     Gets the rank confidence of a specific source. This value within [0,1] measures how much the rank provided by a
specific source is trusted. A value of 0 means the source rank must be ignored. A value of 1 means the source
rank is reliable and must be taken into account. <br>Note: use {@link #needsSrcTypeForSrcBonus(String)} to check
whether the source type is required or if {@link IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_UNDEFINED} value is sufficient.

@param sourceName The name of the source.
@param sourceType The type of the source ({@link IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_DOCBASE}, {@link
                  IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_EXTERNAL}).
@return The rank confidence of the source (real number within [0,1]).

     Indicates whether the type of sources must be provided to the method {@link #getRankConfidence}. If this method
returns <code>false</code> then {@link IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_UNDEFINED} value may be provided as parameter of
the method {@link #getRankConfidence}.

@param sourceName The name of the source.
@return <code>true</code> if the type of sources must be provided; <code>false</code> if {@link
        IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_UNDEFINED} value is sufficient.

     Gets a specific source confidence bonus for queries with attribute constraint. More details at {@link
#getSourceBonusFullText(String)}

@param sourceName The name of the source.
@param sourceType The type of the source ({@link IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_DOCBASE}, {@link
                  IDfSearchSource#SRC_TYPE_EXTERNAL}).
@return The source confidence bonus for queries with attribute constraint.

